      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the goblin analogy. To answer your question, the 90-minute layover in LHR is a relatively short time, but it's doable. Here are some practical tips for making the transfer:\n\nFor the terminal transfer, you'll need to go from one terminal to another. Heathrow has two main terminals, Terminal 2 (for some airlines) and Terminal 5 (for others). Check your airline's website or your boarding pass to see which terminal you'll be arriving at. If you're arriving at Terminal 2, you'll need to go to Terminal 5, and vice versa.\n\nFor security, you'll need to clear security again, but since you're not checking in for your next flight, you won't need to go through the full security process. You can usually just go through a quick security check, like a goblin slipping through a narrow opening.\n\nTo make the most of your 90-minute layover, consider the following:\n\n* Plan your route in advance, and make sure you know which terminal you need to go to.\n* Leave plenty of time to get to your gate, and consider checking the airport's app or website for any flight updates or gate changes.\n*",
